In an article for MailOnline, Young's CEO Patrick Dardis claimed that "Public Health England says pubs and restaurants account for less than three per cent of [Covid-19] transmissions."

This is a misreading of PHE data, as we have written about before ▼

text.1:
We’ve seen claims on social media that the government has stopped contact tracing in schools.

This is not true. Single cases linked to educational settings are now traced centrally, instead of locally.
